  <section>
    <h2>CSS Reference</h2>
    <code-block language="css" show-lines label="kbd CSS">{{ kbdCssCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <p>The border and <code>box-shadow</code> create a 3D key-cap appearance. VB also sets <code>translate: no</code> on <code>&lt;kbd&gt;</code> via the <a href="/docs/i18n/">i18n system</a> to prevent machine translation from breaking key names.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Some screen readers announce <code>&lt;kbd&gt;</code> content as keyboard input</li>
      <li>Use the plus symbol (+) between keys in combinations for clarity</li>
      <li>Provide context: "Press <kbd>X</kbd> to do Y"</li>
      <li>Document shortcuts in a discoverable location</li>
      <li>Always provide alternative methods for keyboard-shortcut-only actions</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Components Using kbd</h2>
    <p>VB web components that display keyboard shortcuts use <code>&lt;kbd&gt;</code> styling:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/custom-elements/short-cuts/"><code>&lt;short-cuts&gt;</code></a> &mdash; Keyboard shortcuts reference modal</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/custom-elements/command-palette/"><code>&lt;command-palette&gt;</code></a> &mdash; Shows shortcut hints alongside commands</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

